    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Romans",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 14,
        "summary": "Avoid quarreling about opinions and making unrighteous judgment of each other\u2014Every knee will bow to Christ\u2014The kingdom of God embraces righteousness, peace, and joy in the Holy Ghost.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Him that is weak in the faith receive ye, but not to doubtful disputations.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 35:3; Rom. 15:1 (1\u20133); 1\u00a0Cor. 8:9; Gal. 6:1; D&C 81:5; 84:106.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Doubt.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disputations.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For one believeth that he may eat all things: another, who is weak, eateth herbs.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0vegetables.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let not him that eateth despise him that eateth not; and let not him which eateth not judge him that eateth: for God hath received him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 2:16.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who art thou that judgest another man's servant? to his own master he standeth or falleth. Yea, he shall be holden up: for God is able to make him stand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 11:12.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "One man esteemeth one day above another: another esteemeth every day alike. Let every man be fully persuaded in his own mind.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 4:10 (9\u201310).",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that regardeth the day, regardeth it unto the Lord; and he that regardeth not the day, to the Lord he doth not regard it. He that eateth, eateth to the Lord, for he giveth God thanks; and he that eateth not, to the Lord he eateth not, and giveth God thanks.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For none of us liveth to himself, and no man dieth to himself.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 5:15 (14\u201316); Gal. 2:20.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For whether we live, we live unto the Lord; and whether we die, we die unto the Lord: whether we live therefore, or die, we are the Lord's.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:44 (44\u201347); 63:49.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For to this end Christ both died, and rose, and revived, that he might be Lord both of the dead and living.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of; Jesus Christ, Power of.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 20:38. TG\u00a0Genealogy and Temple Work; Salvation for the Dead.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1435
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But why dost thou judge thy brother? or why dost thou set at nought thy brother? for we shall all stand before the judgment seat of Christ.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment, the Last.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For it is written, As I live, saith the Lord, every knee shall bow to me, and every tongue shall confess to God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 45:23; Philip. 2:10.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0praise, profess openly.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "So then every one of us shall give account of himself to God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let us not therefore judge one another any more: but judge this rather, that no man put a stumblingblock or an occasion to fall in his brother's way.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 19:14; 1\u00a0Cor. 8:9 (9\u201313); 10:32 (24\u201333); 2\u00a0Cor. 6:3; Alma 39:11.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I know, and am persuaded by the Lord Jesus, that there is nothing unclean of itself: but to him that esteemeth any thing to be unclean, to him it is unclean.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0ceremonially unclean. TG\u00a0Uncleanness.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Motivations.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 143,
                        "end": 148
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But if thy brother be grieved with thy meat, now walkest thou not charitably. Destroy not him with thy meat, for whom Christ died.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Rom. 14:15 \u2026 thou walkest not charitably if thou eatest. Therefore destroy not him with thy meat\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0according to love.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0on account of food.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let not then your good be evil spoken of:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the kingdom of God is not meat and drink; but righteousness, and peace, and joy in the Holy Ghost.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0food. TG\u00a0Food.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contentment; Peace of God.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Joy.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For he that in these things serveth Christ is acceptable to God, and approved of men.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let us therefore follow after the things which make for peace, and things wherewith one may edify another.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace; Peacemakers.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Edification.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For meat destroy not the work of God. All things indeed are pure; but it is evil for that man who eateth with offence.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0Because of food.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Works of.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is good neither to eat flesh, nor to drink wine, nor any thing whereby thy brother stumbleth, or is offended, or is made weak.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 8:13.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hast thou faith? have it to thyself before God. Happy is he that condemneth not himself in that thing which he alloweth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0by what he tries, approves.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he that doubteth is damned if he eat, because he eateth not of faith: for whatsoever is not of faith is sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Doubt.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 104
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}